quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  24,11,"Verily those who brought forward the calumny were a small band among Deem it not an evil for you; nay, it was good for you. Unto every one of them shall be that which he hath earned of the sin, and he among them who undertook the bulk of it---for him shall be a torment mighty"
  24,12,"Wherefore, when ye heard it, did not the believing men and believing women imagine best of their own people and say: this is a calumny manifest"
  24,13,"Wherefore did they not bring four witnesses thereof? Then when they brought not the witnesses, those! with Allah they are the liars"
  24,14,"Had there not been Allah's grace upon you and His mercy in the World and the Hereafter, surely there would have touched you for that whcrein ye had rushed, torment mighty"
  24,15,"When ye were publishing it with your tongues and saying that with your mouths of which ye had no knowledge. Ye deemed it light, and it was with Allah mighty"
  24,16,"And wherefore, when ye heard it, did ye not say: it is not for us to speak thereof, hallowed be Thou! that is a slander mighty"
  24,17,"Allah exhorteth you lest ye may ever revert to the like thereof, if ye are believers indeed"
  24,18,"And Allah expoundeth unto you the revelations and Allah is Knowing, wise"
  24,19,"Verily those who love that in decency should be propagated regarding those who believe, for them shall be a torment afflictive in the world and the Hereafter. And Allah knoweth, and ye know not"
  24,20,"And had there not been Allah's grace upon you and His mercy, and that Allah was Tender and Merciful, ye had Perished"